It's also a collection of
Egyptian art and mummies.

00:14:22.716 --> 00:14:25.799
(smooth tempo music)

00:14:28.490 --> 00:14:30.328
We just moved through the Vatican museum.

00:14:30.328 --> 00:14:33.437
It's series of hallways and corridors

00:14:33.437 --> 00:14:37.573
and not only are there
just amazing sculptures

00:14:37.573 --> 00:14:41.447
on both sides as well as
different exhibits and galleries

00:14:41.447 --> 00:14:44.426
but if you look up, you
will notice paintings

00:14:44.426 --> 00:14:49.033
and decorations and it's just
a museum within a museum,

00:14:49.033 --> 00:14:50.033
of a museum.

00:14:52.353 --> 00:14:54.754
We have entered into the maps gallery

00:14:54.754 --> 00:14:57.271
and this is a long hall that includes maps

00:14:57.271 --> 00:14:58.818
which are painted on both sides.

00:14:58.818 --> 00:15:00.444
There are topographical maps

00:15:00.444 --> 00:15:03.548
which dates back to around 1580.

00:15:03.548 --> 00:15:06.465
(soft tempo music)

00:15:16.052 --> 00:15:17.843
I'm now walking through the Raphael Rooms

00:15:17.843 --> 00:15:20.081
which are a series of four rooms

00:15:20.081 --> 00:15:24.471
which contain just incredibly
beautiful and detailed Frescos

00:15:24.471 --> 00:15:26.267
which were painted by Raphael.

00:15:26.267 --> 00:15:28.738
One of the most famous paintings Frescos

00:15:28.738 --> 00:15:32.567
in the Raphael Rooms is
The School of Athens.

00:15:32.567 --> 00:15:36.756
It's right behind me and
it was painted in 1509

00:15:36.756 --> 00:15:39.399
and it's within the room of the Segnatura.

00:15:39.399 --> 00:15:42.482
(upbeat tempo music)

00:15:44.845 --> 00:15:47.453
We are about to enter the
place that nobody misses

00:15:47.453 --> 00:15:50.586
when they visit the
museums at the Vatican.

00:15:50.586 --> 00:15:54.586
(people chatting in background)

00:15:56.034 --> 00:15:57.535
I think that's the only
place in the whole museum

00:15:57.535 --> 00:15:59.810
where you're not allowed to video or photo

00:15:59.810 --> 00:16:00.977
but it is a...

00:16:02.818 --> 00:16:06.683
It's not a huge chapel but
the ceiling is extremely high

00:16:06.683 --> 00:16:10.056
and it can fit about 2,000
people from what I read

00:16:10.056 --> 00:16:13.719
but you look up and the
walls and on the ceiling

00:16:13.719 --> 00:16:15.587
and it is just...

00:16:15.587 --> 00:16:18.313
All of those paintings by Michelangelo,

00:16:18.313 --> 00:16:21.817
the Frescos that you have seen in photos,

00:16:21.817 --> 00:16:25.231
it's incredible to gaze
into those paintings

00:16:25.231 --> 00:16:26.124
and those Frescos.

00:16:26.124 --> 00:16:28.929
What struck me is how high the ceiling is

00:16:28.929 --> 00:16:30.432
and then just looking up

00:16:30.432 --> 00:16:33.813
and you can just almost fall into a dream

00:16:33.813 --> 00:16:36.458
looking at the Sistine Chapel ceiling.

00:16:36.458 --> 00:16:40.067
(upbeat tempo music)

00:16:40.067 --> 00:16:41.820
We are on our way out of the museum

00:16:41.820 --> 00:16:45.659
and going down the famous
spiral staircase now.

00:16:45.659 --> 00:16:48.256
It took us a little over two hours

00:16:48.256 --> 00:16:50.865
and I think we went pretty fast.

00:16:50.865 --> 00:16:53.671
You can definitely spend
a lot more time in there

00:16:53.671 --> 00:16:57.008
if you took more time to
look at all of the art work

00:16:57.008 --> 00:16:58.678
and the galleries and the paintings.

00:16:58.678 --> 00:17:01.936
We are now walking over
to St. Peter's Basilica.

00:17:01.936 --> 00:17:05.276
One of the things I want
to do is to climb the dome.

00:17:05.276 --> 00:17:06.594
Michelangelo's famous dome

00:17:06.594 --> 00:17:09.321
on the top of St. Peter's Basilica.

00:17:09.321 --> 00:17:12.049
So we got in the line for the dome

00:17:12.049 --> 00:17:14.284
and I think it is a separate line

00:17:14.284 --> 00:17:17.704
from entering into the
actual main Basilica.

00:17:17.704 --> 00:17:20.425
So that security point ended up getting us

00:17:20.425 --> 00:17:21.687
into the Basilica as well.

00:17:21.687 --> 00:17:23.840
I thought it was just
gonna get us into the dome.

00:17:23.840 --> 00:17:26.236
So we're going to enter the Basilica first

00:17:26.236 --> 00:17:27.986
and then go to the dome afterwards.

00:17:27.986 --> 00:17:31.403
(soft percussion music)

00:17:34.467 --> 00:17:36.825
It is massive in here

00:17:36.825 --> 00:17:38.942
and I can see the dome up ahead

00:17:38.942 --> 00:17:40.692
and I can see the rays of sunshine

00:17:40.692 --> 00:17:42.849
shinning down through the dome.

00:17:42.849 --> 00:17:45.861
St. Peter's Basilica
was designed by Bramante

00:17:45.861 --> 00:17:47.694
and also Michelangelo

00:17:47.694 --> 00:17:50.256
and it is one of the most impressive sites

00:17:50.256 --> 00:17:52.412
in the Vatican city.

00:17:52.412 --> 00:17:54.403
Especially notable for its dome.

00:17:54.403 --> 00:17:55.705
I'm gonna go climb the dome now

00:17:55.705 --> 00:17:59.872
and hopefully get some great
views of Rome from here.

00:18:01.045 --> 00:18:03.490
And the amount of marble and the carvings

00:18:03.490 --> 00:18:07.235
and sculptures that it took
to create this Basilica

00:18:07.235 --> 00:18:08.495
is mind blowing.

00:18:08.495 --> 00:18:11.578
(upbeat tempo music)

00:18:15.692 --> 00:18:17.680
I just got my ticket.

00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:21.299
I am going to climb the
stairs to the top of the dome.

00:18:21.299 --> 00:18:24.794
It is a total of 551 steps to the top.

00:18:24.794 --> 00:18:27.971
So here we go. Here we start.

00:18:27.971 --> 00:18:31.054
(upbeat tempo music)

00:18:32.157 --> 00:18:35.248
As busy and packed as the Basilica is,

00:18:35.248 --> 00:18:36.202
I'm in the staircase now

00:18:36.202 --> 00:18:39.132
and it's completely quiet.

00:18:39.132 --> 00:18:41.209
There's nobody else here

00:18:41.209 --> 00:18:44.263
and I should also mention
that you can take the elevator

00:18:44.263 --> 00:18:46.591
at least part of the way up

00:18:46.591 --> 00:18:48.080
and then just climb a little bit.

00:18:48.080 --> 00:18:48.978
I just took a few minutes

00:18:48.978 --> 00:18:52.811
and I've come to some
outdoor courtyard level.

00:18:57.475 --> 00:18:59.594
I didn't even know we
were going to have a view

00:18:59.594 --> 00:19:00.490
from the top of the dome

00:19:00.490 --> 00:19:03.733
but on the inside of the dome.

00:19:03.733 --> 00:19:06.176
Wow, this is awesome, you can see below.

00:19:06.176 --> 00:19:09.259
(upbeat tempo music)

00:19:11.786 --> 00:19:12.841
Made it to that first level

00:19:12.841 --> 00:19:17.358
and those are some amazing
views of the church from above

00:19:17.358 --> 00:19:22.284
but now climbing the circular
staircase to the cupola.

00:19:22.284 --> 00:19:24.784
It's a pretty tight staircase.

00:19:26.426 --> 00:19:27.767
I just made it to the top of the dome

00:19:27.767 --> 00:19:30.330
and that took exactly 13 minutes

00:19:30.330 --> 00:19:33.868
and there were some
amazing spiral staircases.

00:19:33.868 --> 00:19:36.951
(upbeat tempo music)

00:19:49.849 --> 00:19:52.856
From the top here, you have
a full 360 view of Rome

00:19:52.856 --> 00:19:54.974
so you could walk around the dome.

00:19:54.974 --> 00:19:57.948
You can see the edges of
the dome going downwards,

00:19:57.948 --> 00:19:59.455
sloping downwards.

00:19:59.455 --> 00:20:02.257
And of course you have a
whole view, an entire view,

00:20:02.257 --> 00:20:04.821
of St. Peters square from above.

00:20:04.821 --> 00:20:07.904
(upbeat tempo music)

00:20:10.355 --> 00:20:12.772
(bell rings)

00:20:13.610 --> 00:20:16.222
The 360 views of Rome were amazing

00:20:16.222 --> 00:20:19.768
and also just the hike up
the stairs to get to the top

00:20:19.768 --> 00:20:21.717
was also a lot of fun.

00:20:21.717 --> 00:20:24.447
I would highly recommend
fishing out the extra money

00:20:24.447 --> 00:20:27.047
when you come to St. Peters.

00:20:27.047 --> 00:20:27.978
We are walking to the bus stop

00:20:27.978 --> 00:20:30.012
and gonna try to take the
bus to the Jewish ghetto

00:20:30.012 --> 00:20:31.595
for dinner tonight.

00:20:34.895 --> 00:20:35.793
Oh and how convenient.

00:20:35.793 --> 00:20:37.879
The bus that we need to take

00:20:37.879 --> 00:20:39.319
pulled up right as we got here.

00:20:39.319 --> 00:20:42.402
(upbeat tempo music)

00:20:48.753 --> 00:20:51.231
And it should be just
a short walk from here

00:20:51.231 --> 00:20:52.613
to the Jewish area.

00:20:52.613 --> 00:20:55.696
(upbeat tempo music)

00:20:57.413 --> 00:20:59.492
I don't know too much about the influence

00:20:59.492 --> 00:21:01.480
and the history of Jews in Rome

00:21:01.480 --> 00:21:04.527
but I do know that there
has been a Jewish influence

00:21:04.527 --> 00:21:06.316
for many years

00:21:06.316 --> 00:21:08.635
and this Jewish area of Rome

00:21:08.635 --> 00:21:11.766
was officially established back in 1555.

00:21:11.766 --> 00:21:14.082
There are a number of different
Jewish Italian restaurants

00:21:14.082 --> 00:21:15.137
in this area.

00:21:15.137 --> 00:21:17.617
I chose to come to one called Nonna Betta.

00:21:17.617 --> 00:21:20.150
- [Ying] Thank you.
- [Mark] Thank you.

00:21:20.150 --> 00:21:22.622
One of the most famous Roman Jewish dishes

00:21:22.622 --> 00:21:25.347
or it's kind of like a appetizer starter

00:21:25.347 --> 00:21:27.418
is a fried artichoke.

00:21:27.418 --> 00:21:30.226
They are deep fried so they're crispy.

00:21:30.226 --> 00:21:32.545
You can see that little
bit of salt on top.

00:21:32.545 --> 00:21:34.295
This looks fantastic.

00:21:35.246 --> 00:21:38.273
You can actually see how
the inside is gonna be nice

00:21:38.273 --> 00:21:40.917
and probable soft while the
outside is gonna be crispy

00:21:40.917 --> 00:21:41.917
and crunchy.

00:21:43.033 --> 00:21:46.783
Let me try to grab all
those layers together.

00:21:53.933 --> 00:21:57.316
Oh yeah, the inside is
creamy like cooked eggplant

00:21:57.316 --> 00:21:59.847
and then those outer layers are crispy

00:21:59.847 --> 00:22:01.999
and a little bit chewy

00:22:01.999 --> 00:22:03.709
and then it's just nicely salted.

00:22:03.709 --> 00:22:05.948
Actually, those outer
leaves are the artichoke.

00:22:05.948 --> 00:22:07.817
They were a little too chewy to chew

00:22:07.817 --> 00:22:09.449
so I probably ate it wrong

00:22:09.449 --> 00:22:10.384
because it's an artichoke

00:22:10.384 --> 00:22:12.801
so it has those really chewy,

00:22:13.760 --> 00:22:17.049
outer leaf-like things of the artichoke

00:22:17.049 --> 00:22:19.635
so the inside is really soft

00:22:19.635 --> 00:22:22.439
and then you sort of eat all
that meat from those leaves.

00:22:22.439 --> 00:22:24.350
I think I approached the artichoke

00:22:24.350 --> 00:22:26.262
a little wrong in the first place

00:22:26.262 --> 00:22:27.847
because I was thinking that,

00:22:27.847 --> 00:22:30.171
because it's fried,
those would all be soft

00:22:30.171 --> 00:22:31.881
but they're still a little bit chewy

00:22:31.881 --> 00:22:35.776
but what you do so you can
just grab those crispy bits

00:22:35.776 --> 00:22:36.693
and then...

00:22:39.157 --> 00:22:40.784
Just like any artichoke,

00:22:40.784 --> 00:22:44.951
still bite off all of that
gooey soft bit from the bottom.

00:22:48.272 --> 00:22:52.670
And you can eat the crispy
piece of the artichoke as well

00:22:52.670 --> 00:22:55.886
but definitely don't make
the mistake like I did

00:22:55.886 --> 00:22:58.815
and take half that artichoke in one bite

00:22:58.815 --> 00:23:00.074
or you won't be able to chew it.

00:23:00.074 --> 00:23:00.970
That's for sure.

00:23:00.970 --> 00:23:03.366
And also to begin with
we got a cup of pasta.

00:23:03.366 --> 00:23:07.429
And this is, I think it's the
Nonna Betta special pasta.

00:23:07.429 --> 00:23:11.346
Let me try to work on my
pasta twirling skills.

00:23:12.432 --> 00:23:15.849
I think it's a type of minced meat sauce.

00:23:23.830 --> 00:23:25.310
Yeah, that's really nice too

00:23:25.310 --> 00:23:27.015
and it's mostly tomato based

00:23:27.015 --> 00:23:30.395
but it has a little bit
of a creaminess to it

00:23:30.395 --> 00:23:33.221
so I'm not sure what else is in there.

00:23:33.221 --> 00:23:34.426
Really good with those noodles

00:23:34.426 --> 00:23:37.236
and then just with little
bits of minced meat.

00:23:37.236 --> 00:23:38.253
Let me get one more bite of this.

00:23:38.253 --> 00:23:39.753
This is excellent.

00:23:43.341 --> 00:23:46.433
I think I'm getting
better at my pasta twirl.

00:23:46.433 --> 00:23:49.433
But I definitely need a lot of work.

00:23:53.022 --> 00:23:54.689
Main course has arrived.

